Popular Nigerian rapper, Folarin Falana, famously known as Falz, has reacted to the viral video of Diezani Alison-Madueke, a former Minister of Petroleum Resources, saying that internet fraudsters, otherwise known as Yahoo Boys, have become role models in Nigerian society. Diezani warned that the new trend ‘Yahoo Yahoo’ is a travesty of an unfolding tragedy for Nigeria, adding that only hard work could guarantee success. The former minister said this while delivering a lecture at a virtual event organized by the Ijaw National Development Group. Her statement has since stirred reactions from Nigerians, especially coming from a former minister who is under trial for alleged fraud. Reacting, Falz slammed Diezani, adding that the former minister is on the run and her mouth is still running. Sharing a photo of Diezani, Falz wrote on Instagram on Monday: “You are on the run, but your mouth still dey run. Who be Yahoo Yahoo girl if no be you?